<ABS>  Japan Fiscal Year 1993 Budgets for Science and Technology </ABS>
<DATE1>   24 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100></F>
<H3> <TI>     Science Council of Japan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  93FE0950B Tokyo GAKUJUTSU GEPPO in Japanese Jul 93 pp 28-29 </F>
<F P=103> 93FE0950B </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo GAKUJUTSU GEPPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] 
  The aim of the Science Council of Japan (SCJ), "as an 
organization that represents Japan's scientists at home and 
abroad, is to advance science and to make science reflect in and 
permeate through the administration, industry, and the 
lifestyles of the Japanese people." 
  The total SCJ budget for FY93 is &yen;1,095.827 million, 
which is &yen;53.345 million less than its FY92 budget of 
&yen;1,042.482 million. 
  The main increases in the SCJ budget were in the 
Consultation-Related Expenses and International Scientific 
Exchange Expenses (international contributions, and sponsoring 
the Asia Scientific Conference (temporary name)). There were 
decreases in International Scientific Exchange Expenses for 
holding conferences within Japan. 
  The budget amounts are shown in the table below, and an 
outline of the major items follows. 



  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|FY93 Budget                                                                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                  |(Unit: &yen;1,000)                                      | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Item              |FY92 budget       |FY93 budget       |Relative increase/| 
|                  |                  |                  |decrease          | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|1. Consultation-R-|248,789           |265,525           |16,736            | 
|elated Expenses   |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
