<H5>  2. R&amp;D To Cope with Advanced, Diversified Consumer Needs </H5>
  The MAFF will develop models for predicting fluctuations in 
the major vegetable supply and demand, and will implement new 
R&amp;D for contributing to supply and demand stability. In 
addition, the MAFF will continue work on the "development of new 
wetland crops for expanding demand" (the Super Rice Project), 
which will contribute to expanding the demand for rice, and the 
"development of technology for improving the quality and 
productivity of wetland wheat crops," with priority given to the 
cultivation of wheat varieties that surpass foreign-produced 
wheat (ASW). 


