<H3> <TI>   MITI-Affiliated Utilities Federation To Open Washington 
Office for Information Gathering </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P60067A Tokyo NIKKEI SANGYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Jul 93 
p 15 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94P60067A </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIKKEI SANGYO SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The Federation of Electric Power Companies (Kohei 
Abe, chairman) will establish a Washington, D.C., office as 
early as this fall. The decision was made at the 21 July meeting 
of the chairmen of the nine electric power companies. Along with 
gathering information on such issues as U.S. atomic power and 
environmental policies, the office will also actively generate 
news on Japan's energy situation. Tokyo Electric Power Company 
and other utilities have overseas offices, but this will be the 
federation's first overseas office. 

</TEXT>

