<DATE1>   27 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> Chemical Engineering </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sumitomo Chemical Restarts Epoxy Resin Plant Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94FE0180B Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO in Japanese 8 Nov 93 p 1 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 94FE0180B </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KAGAKU KOGYO NIPPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text]The Niihama Plant epoxy facilities of Sumitomo 
Chemical Co., Ltd. will restart operations in a day or two and 
are expected to begin shipping in mid-December. On 4 November, 
Niihama city decided to remove the plant stoppage order; 
Sumitomo Chemical, which received that order, is expected to 
restart operations in a day or two and to switch to a shipping 
system in December over a trial operating period of about one 
month. As a result, the prospect for shipping restart from the 
end of this year to the beginning of next year is premature. 
  Since Sumitomo Chemical's orthocresolnovolak epoxy fire, 
voices wishing for the early restarting of the semiconductor 
sealing material market have strengthened. While operations to 
restart the plant are advancing smoothly and the turmoil in the 
market during this period was avoided because of shipping 
support from another company in the same industry, the restart 
time of this plant was noted. Because of the stoppage canceling 
order of the local Niihama city, the operation of novolak 
facilities was restarted. This month it is expected to switch to 
trial operations to receive sample shipping and user evaluation 
and to make full scale shipping at the beginning of December. 

</TEXT>

